{"word":"competere","priority":"☆☆☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"(ラテン語) 競争する、競う、匹敵する、要求する、同時に存在する","english_definition":"(Latin) to compete, contend, strive for the same object, be a rival; to be a match for, be equal to; to demand, claim; to exist at the same time.","examples":[{"sentence":"Multi ad honores competunt.","translation":"多くの人々が名誉を求めて競争する。"},{"sentence":"Virtus cum fortuna non semper competit.","translation":"美徳は常に幸運と匹敵するとは限らない。"},{"sentence":"Avaritia et fides difficile competunt.","translation":"貪欲と誠実さは同時に存在しにくい。"}],"collocations":["cum aliquo competere (～と競争する)","ad aliquid competere (～を要求する)","honores competere (名誉を求める)"],"synonyms":["certare","pugnare","aemulari","contendere","postulare","exigere","simul esse"],"antonyms":[]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の「com-」（共に）+「petere」（求める、目指す）に由来する。元々は「共に何かを目指す」という意味合いから、競争や要求といった意味に発展した。","priority":"★★★"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/komˈpe.te.re/","syllables":"com-pe-te-re"},"inflection":{"verb_forms":{"present_infinitive":"competere","present_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"competo","2nd_person_singular":"competis","3rd_person_singular":"competit","1st_person_plural":"competimus","2nd_person_plural":"competitis","3rd_person_plural":"competunt"},"imperfect_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"competebam","2nd_person_singular":"competebas","3rd_person_singular":"competebat","1st_person_plural":"competebamus","2nd_person_plural":"competebatis","3rd_person_plural":"competebant"},"future_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"competam","2nd_person_singular":"competes","3rd_person_singular":"competet","1st_person_plural":"competemus","2nd_person_plural":"competetis","3rd_person_plural":"competent"},"perfect_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"competivi","2nd_person_singular":"competivisti","3rd_person_singular":"competivit","1st_person_plural":"competivimus","2nd_person_plural":"competivistis","3rd_person_plural":"competiverunt"},"pluperfect_indicative":{"1st_person_singular":"competiveram","2